 Dawn took a few moments to clean her hands, and then with her freshly made golden dagger, basically sterile, she began to open Aly's stomach, but not after the proper numbing..BARK. Dawn knew better than to use spells. She gently opened up Aly's stomach to see the tiny baby boy..her head shook lightly as she put her dagger down in Ara's hands.<br>
<br>
&quot;Um Aly....the cord is wrapped around his neck...&quot;<br>
<br>
 There was no other way for Dawn to explain it, she gently took the child from the womb(?), Dawn's hands gently unwrapped the cord from the child's neck. Each movement she held him closer until the cord was gone from its neck, and Dawn's hand supported his neck. Then the dagger cut the the cord and a happy WAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA was heard through the silen Tavern. Dawn smiled handing the child to Ara. Her hands quickly worked to sew Aly's stomach shut. Once done she spoke again.<br>
<br>
&quot;Congradulations Aly. You have just given birth to a son.&quot;<br>
