lass=m><span class=title> Re: Birth of the Amazon Glory</span><hr size=1>  They always say the surprise is the best part about the kill, and believe me Dawn believes every part of that. She had watched the man enter, draw his sword, and speak. Each movement had angered Dawn, which caused a loud roar to erupt from her mouth. It sounded as though it came from Hades himself, it emitted from only her throat, but what strong tiger wouldn't roar like she did. Dawn moved to grab her sword but it wasn't at her side, causing her to realize it was by Aly. With a few jumps as she ran, she flipped quickly ontop of a table, and continued her running toward the couch, she rolled off of a table, and grabbed her sword, and backflipped off of the back of the couch to land just behind the Roman fool. She spin jumped into the air, her foot knocking the man to the side and into the table next to him as she came down.<br>
<br>
 &quot;You fool. You think you can come into THIS TAVERN..and kill my rite of caste, and her child. Not a good move. I hate men and I surely hate Roman men. You need to back off.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Dawn stood in a strong attack stance, her green eyes had quickly changed to red in the threat of a fight. Andrenline pulsed through her veins as she growled again, growing more angery and more fierce with the moment. She watched as the man stood to look at her...the sight of the weary and weak soldier made her chuckle maniacally. <br>
<br>
 &quot;Weak.&quot;<br>
<br>
 That was the last word Dawn spoke as she sprung forward, her sword slicing across his chest as her foot met with his groin to push him against the wall. Dawn quickly dropped her sword, as the daggers around her wrist were flipped to face him, then thrusted into his shoulders, were Dawn twisted them deeper until they met with the bone. Her eyes grew happy as well as her lips as he cried out in pain.<br>
<br>
 &quot;I always knew Romans were the most fun to kill.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Yes, Dawn was cold blooded, what would you expect from an Assassin of her stature. She slowly retwisted the daggers, causing them to unscrew from the bone and pull from his flesh, ripping muscles and ligiments more as they came out. The daggers made the wound so much worse than it would have been if just thrusted. She smiled as she stabbed the same bloody daggers into his stomach, where they were left. Bloody hands felt warm and at home with her fighting spirit.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Weak Romans, such a threat. NOT&quot;<br>
<br>
 Dawn sounded like a kid again, as her hands held against the strangers shoulders, and thumbs gently pushed into the shoulder wounds, and dug dangerously around, pushing and tearing at anything they felt, then they made it to the bone, were Dawn pushed up with her knee on the man's crotch area, sliding him up the wall and her thumbs and arms pushed down into the wound, breaking the bones. It caused a sickening crack to roar through the Tavern. Then without notice Dawn pulled away from the man, she flipped forward onto a table and then turned, and kicked him across the face.<br>
<br>
 &quot;You can tell your Roman friends, to never entire this Tavern again...oh wait..you won't live that long!&quot;<br>
<br>
 She cackled softly, unsheathing another two daggers from around elven boots. Dawn sat casually on the table and sent the daggers sailing into the man's thighs. Another painful howl filled the ears of the people in the Tavern.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Does it hurt? Cause I'm enjoying it.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Dawn stood once again, grabbing the man by the throat, throwing him across the Tavern into the sturdy bar. Where she walked to face him, she just stood there, watching the man in pain, watching him die. He was minutes away.<br>
